	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "He succeeded his father King ʾIyāsu II in 1755. \n                  He was seven years old when he became a king and his grandmother, the famous Gondarian queen Bǝrhān Mogasā,  continued to act as his regent. \n                  Throughout his reign, he was only a figurehead and the real political power remained in the hand of the queen Bǝrhān Mogasā. \n               " .
